# ease-scroll-driven-animations

**EaseMotion CSS · Scroll-Driven Animation Utilities**
Submitted for GSSoC 2026 · [Issue #13395](https://github.com/SAPTARSHI-coder/EaseMotion-css/issues/13395)

---

## What This Adds

A set of utility classes that tie existing EaseMotion CSS animations directly to the browser's native **CSS Scroll-Driven Animations API** — no JavaScript, no GSAP, no IntersectionObserver.

Two scroll timeline types are supported:

| Timeline type | CSS API used | Use case |
|---|---|---|
| **View timeline** — `.em-scroll-view` | `animation-timeline: view()` | Animate elements as they enter the viewport |
| **Scroll timeline** — `.em-scroll-timeline` | `animation-timeline: scroll(root)` | Animate relative to the total page scroll position |

